external_knowledge:
- 'Top 10 best-selling products' refers to the products with the highest total sales in each region;
- 'Cumulative sales value' is the sum of the total sales of the top 10 products in each region;
- 'Bustling marketplace' is a metaphor for a region where products are actively sold and purchased.

- "Star customer" refers to the customer with the highest total sales among those who have purchased the top-rated, top-selling product in any category;
- "Shone the brightest" refers to the highest total sales;
- "Most coveted and highly-rated product" refers to the product with the highest cumulative sales and an average rating greater than 4.

- '2017' refers to the year the orders were shipped;
- 'orders costing more than $100' means the total cost of the order, including tax and discount, is greater than $100;
- 'highest average discount' is calculated per shipping mode and used to rank the orders.

- 'Top 3 sellers' refers to the products with the highest sales in each category and sub-category;
- 'Quantities greater than 1' means the products were ordered more than once in a single order;
- 'Highest sales' is determined by the sum of sales amounts.

- 'Delivered' refers to orders that have been successfully delivered to the customer;
- 'USA' is the country of interest for this query;
- The total revenue is the sum of the total costs of the orders.

- "top-selling sub-categories" refers to the sub-categories where the product has the highest sales within that sub-category;
- "top 3 selling categories" refers to the categories with the highest total sales, ranked 1 to 3;
- "stars in the constellations of the sales universe" is a metaphor to describe the best-performing products within the best-performing categories.

- "Whales" in commerce often refer to high-value customers or large corporations that generate significant sales;
- "Significant splashes" metaphorically represent the number of orders placed by a customer;
- "Financial waves" metaphorically represent the total sales generated by a customer.

- 'shining star in the galaxy of customers' refers to the customer with the highest total sales;
- 'outshine all others' means having the highest rank in sales;
- 'delivered orders' are orders with the status 'Delivered' and a non-null ship date.

- "Shining stars" refers to products with high sales, good ratings, and few returns;
- "Substantial sales" refers to total sales greater than 1000;
- "Stellar reviews" refers to an average rating greater than 4;
- "Minimal returns" refers to fewer than 5 returns.

'Best category' refers to the category with the highest total sales and average rating.;
'Total sales' include the total cost of orders, which encompasses tax and discounts.;
'Average rating' is calculated from customer reviews on a scale of 1 to 5 stars.
